@endpoint POST /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/servers/{serverName}/databases/{databaseName}/operations/{operationId}/cancel
@desc Cancels the asynchronous operation on the database.
@required {resourceGroupName: any # The name of the resource group that contains the resource. You can obtain this value from the Azure Resource Manager API or the portal., serverName: any # The name of the server., databaseName: any # The name of the database., operationId: any # The operation identifier., subscriptionId: any # The subscription ID that identifies an Azure subscription., api-version: any # The API version to use for the request.}
@returns(200) The request for cancel has been executed successfully.

@endpoint GET /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/servers/{serverName}/databases/{databaseName}/operations
@desc Gets a list of operations performed on the database.
@required {resourceGroupName: any # The name of the resource group that contains the resource. You can obtain this value from the Azure Resource Manager API or the portal., serverName: any # The name of the server., databaseName: any # The name of the database., subscriptionId: any # The subscription ID that identifies an Azure subscription., api-version: any # The API version to use for the request.}
@returns(200) The request for getting database operations has been executed successfully.

@end
